          <LEXCollocations>
            <LEXCollocation>κεφαλὴ γωνίας</LEXCollocation>
          </LEXCollocations>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-06 12:44:50" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a set phrase, literally: head of the corner) the cornerstone or capstone of a building, essential to its construction (κεφαλὴ γωνίας occurs in the NT only figuratively in reference to Christ)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>cornerstone</Gloss>
                <Gloss>important stone</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though some scholars have thought that κεφαλὴ γωνίας refers to a keystone of an arch or the lintel stone over a door, it is highly probable that κεφαλὴ γωνίας has essentially the same meaning as ἀκρογωνιαῖος.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
